        "author": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2010-12-27 05:35:20.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Bob Glossman",
          "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
          "date": "2012-11-12 18:19:53.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-32 osd: keep root node BH ref of IAM container",
        "message": "LU-32 osd: keep root node BH ref of IAM container\n\nIAM in ldiskfs-osd will always consume some slots in bh_lru (see:\nfs/buffer.c), if we keep buffer_head reference on root node,\nwe can save one slot in bh_lru and could be somehow helpful for\noverall performance, I did some tests, LRU hits rate increased\n5%-10% while creating files if we always keep this reference.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I954f26932462169c9bfc6bbfe1a57b5348624179\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/1826\nTested-by: Hudson\nReviewed-by: Bobi Jam <bobijam@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <whamcloud.maloo@gmail.com>\nReviewed-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
  },
